ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It was a good close-up look at the Damascus Document. I would certainly recommend it to another student. It was great to examine one of the Dead Sea Scrolls closely instead of just getting a summary of the what the entire document says.
It's a slow class. I would recommend it to those who are interested in the Scrolls already; not to those for whom this is an intro to the DSS literature.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The Dea Sea Scrolls are a very important texts to comprehend in my field. This was a great seminar that took one of the scrolls and examined what we can learn from it.
